WEBVTT

00:00:02.127 --> 00:00:04.254
<i>The world has become a superhuman society,</i>

00:00:04.421 --> 00:00:08.175
<i>and about 80% of the world's population</i>
<i>now has some kind of special trait.</i>

00:00:08.342 --> 00:00:10.093
<i>In this world swirling with chaos,</i>

00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:13.180
<i>the profession that everyone</i>
<i>once dreamed about and admired</i>

00:00:13.347 --> 00:00:15.140
<i>came into the limelight.</i>

00:00:16.099 --> 00:00:19.478
<i>Heroes of justice fighting villains</i>
<i>and saving people from distress.</i>

00:00:20.938 --> 00:00:26.902
<i>Yes, this is the story of how</i>
<i>I became the greatest hero.</i>

00:01:59.077 --> 00:02:00.037
Midoriya.

00:02:02.706 --> 00:02:03.790
I'm going to beat you.

00:02:09.253 --> 00:02:11.006
The students from the other courses

00:02:11.173 --> 00:02:13.091
are aiming for the top
with everything they've got!

00:02:13.759 --> 00:02:16.762
I can't afford to fall behind.

00:02:18.972 --> 00:02:21.350
I'll be going for it
with everything I have, too.

00:02:28.649 --> 00:02:32.486
IN THEIR OWN QUIRKY WAYS

00:02:33.362 --> 00:02:36.365
<i>The U.A. sports festival</i>
<i>first-year stage qualifier!</i>

00:02:36.782 --> 00:02:40.827
The first game is an obstacle course race!

00:02:40.994 --> 00:02:45.958
It's a cruel chicken race where anything
goes as long as you stay on course!

00:02:46.124 --> 00:02:47.042
Hey.

00:02:47.209 --> 00:02:48.669
We'll bring you the exciting scenes

00:02:48.836 --> 00:02:52.673
<i>-with camera robots set around the course!</i>
<i>-You don't need me, do you?</i>

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:54.675
<i>Now then…</i>

00:02:54.842 --> 00:02:57.678
<i>Can the golden eggs</i>

00:02:57.845 --> 00:03:02.683
<i>aiming to be future heroes</i>
<i>get through the mass of Robo Infernos?</i>

00:03:03.559 --> 00:03:05.561
If they went through all this trouble,

00:03:05.727 --> 00:03:08.355
I wish they would've prepared
something better.

00:03:11.942 --> 00:03:14.152
Since my stupid old man is watching.

00:03:28.834 --> 00:03:30.294
He stopped them!

00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:32.296
Between their legs! We can get through!

00:03:32.796 --> 00:03:33.672
I wouldn't if I were you.

00:03:33.839 --> 00:03:36.466
I froze them when they were unbalanced.

00:03:38.468 --> 00:03:39.636
They'll fall over.

00:03:48.729 --> 00:03:52.733
<i>The first one through the first barrier</i>
<i>is Shoto Todoroki from Class 1-A!</i>

00:03:55.027 --> 00:03:57.196
Hey! Someone's trapped underneath!

00:03:57.613 --> 00:03:58.989
Wouldn't that kill them?

00:03:59.156 --> 00:04:01.158
Will people <i>die</i> at this sports festival?

00:04:05.204 --> 00:04:07.080
Like I'd die!

00:04:07.873 --> 00:04:11.335
<i>Kirishima from Class 1-A</i>
<i>was underneath! That's crazy!</i>

00:04:11.502 --> 00:04:12.878
That bastard, Todoroki!

00:04:13.045 --> 00:04:15.214
He timed it on purpose
so it'd be right when they fell.

00:04:15.380 --> 00:04:17.089
If it hadn't been me,
someone would've died!

00:04:17.841 --> 00:04:20.427
<i>Eijiro Kirishima!</i>
<i>Quirk: Hardening!</i>

00:04:20.969 --> 00:04:23.180
<i>His body can get super hard!</i>

00:04:23.347 --> 00:04:26.183
<i>He can become the strongest spear,</i>
<i>or the strongest shield!</i>

00:04:27.684 --> 00:04:29.603
That Class A…

00:04:30.562 --> 00:04:33.565
really is filled with bastards!

00:04:33.732 --> 00:04:36.151
<i>Tetsutetsu from Class B</i>
<i>was also underneath!</i>

00:04:36.318 --> 00:04:37.611
<i>That's crazy!</i>

00:04:37.778 --> 00:04:39.571
If it hadn't been me,
someone would've died!

00:04:40.531 --> 00:04:43.200
<i>Tetsutetsu Tetsutetsu.</i>
<i>Quirk: Steel!</i>

00:04:43.659 --> 00:04:45.536
<i>His body can become like steel!</i>

00:04:45.702 --> 00:04:48.413
<i>He can become the strongest spear,</i>
<i>or the strongest shield!</i>

00:04:48.580 --> 00:04:50.457
Our Quirks are pretty much the same?

00:04:50.624 --> 00:04:52.000
I have a hard enough time
standing out as it is!

00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:53.752
Wait, you little…

00:04:53.919 --> 00:04:55.754
Those guys are lucky.

00:04:55.921 --> 00:04:57.965
They can get through without
being afraid of getting crushed.

00:04:58.632 --> 00:05:01.677
Anyway, let's work together
for now to clear a path!

00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:05.931
Bakugo?

00:05:06.098 --> 00:05:08.559
<i>Like I'd let you get ahead of me!</i>

00:05:10.686 --> 00:05:12.354
<i>Class 1-A's Bakugo!</i>

00:05:12.521 --> 00:05:14.189
<i>Since the bottom's blocked,</i>
<i>he goes overhead!</i>

00:05:14.565 --> 00:05:15.691
Clever!

00:05:17.359 --> 00:05:20.529
You seem like you'd be
the type to plow straight through,

00:05:20.696 --> 00:05:22.406
but you can go around when you need to,
huh?

00:05:23.073 --> 00:05:25.367
I'm going to hitch a ride!

00:05:27.077 --> 00:05:29.705
<i>Hanta Sero.</i>
<i>Quirk: Tape!</i>

00:05:29.872 --> 00:05:32.040
<i>He can shoot tape-like</i>
<i>material from his elbows!</i>

00:05:32.207 --> 00:05:33.750
<i>He can also wind it up and use it to move!</i>

00:05:33.917 --> 00:05:35.878
<i>Or cut it off and use it as a trap!</i>

00:05:36.587 --> 00:05:38.422
-Land!
-Aye, aye!

00:05:39.631 --> 00:05:42.301
<i>Fumikage Tokoyami.</i>
<i>Quirk: Dark Shadow!</i>

00:05:43.051 --> 00:05:46.180
<i>He's got a shadow-like monster</i>
<i>living inside him</i>

00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:47.848
<i>that can materialize</i>
<i>and change shape elastically!</i>

00:05:53.145 --> 00:05:56.982
As expected, most of the group
that's gone ahead is from Class A.

00:05:58.567 --> 00:06:01.612
Class B and the other courses
aren't bad, either!

00:06:01.945 --> 00:06:02.905
It's just…

00:06:03.488 --> 00:06:05.532
…Class A doesn't spend
a lot of time standing around.

00:06:19.755 --> 00:06:21.840
Those who experienced firsthand

00:06:22.007 --> 00:06:24.635
<i>that world above them through</i>
<i>the incident at USJ…</i>

00:06:24.801 --> 00:06:25.802
Release!

00:06:26.220 --> 00:06:28.430
<i>Those who had fear</i>
<i>planted in their hearts…</i>

00:06:29.431 --> 00:06:31.767
<i>Those who dealt with it</i>
<i>and pulled through…</i>

00:06:32.726 --> 00:06:36.688
They all used that experience
to drown out their hesitation.

00:06:37.564 --> 00:06:40.567
<i>I can't rely on One For All</i>
<i>this early in the competition!</i>

00:06:44.947 --> 00:06:47.032
It's the armor
of the one Todoroki defeated!

00:06:49.201 --> 00:06:52.162
<i>That robot will lock onto</i>
<i>the target and track it.</i>

00:06:52.829 --> 00:06:54.498
<i>I'll make it build up momentum…</i>

00:06:54.665 --> 00:06:56.375
<i>And then…</i>

00:06:56.875 --> 00:06:57.918
<i>It won't be able to stop suddenly!</i>

00:07:00.003 --> 00:07:01.839
<i>Move!</i>

00:07:03.257 --> 00:07:06.677
<i>This can be a shield, too!</i>
<i>It'll be useful!</i>

00:07:15.561 --> 00:07:16.895
Yaoyorozu!

00:07:17.229 --> 00:07:18.438
A piece of cake.

00:07:23.735 --> 00:07:25.195
The path is clear!

00:07:26.321 --> 00:07:28.866
She defeated
those zero-point villains so easily?

00:07:29.408 --> 00:07:31.535
No wonder
she got in through recommendations.

00:07:31.869 --> 00:07:35.706
During the entrance exam,
they were there to be avoided.

00:07:36.206 --> 00:07:40.586
If you see them as things to be defeated,
they're dumb hunks of metal.

00:07:40.752 --> 00:07:42.713
You'll start to see openings.

00:07:44.047 --> 00:07:47.176
I want you to tell the world "I am here!"

00:07:49.178 --> 00:07:51.346
<i>I told him that even though</i>
<i>I knew it'd be unreasonable.</i>

00:07:52.097 --> 00:07:53.515
<i>It doesn't matter if it's close!</i>

00:07:53.849 --> 00:07:55.350
<i>Just get to the next round!</i>

00:07:56.435 --> 00:07:59.062
<i>Hey, hey!</i>
<i>The first barrier's a piece of cake?</i>

00:07:59.938 --> 00:08:02.191
Then what about the second?

00:08:03.942 --> 00:08:05.402
<i>If you fall, you're out!</i>

00:08:05.569 --> 00:08:07.863
<i>If you don't wanna fall, then crawl!</i>

00:08:08.030 --> 00:08:09.907
<i>It's "The Fall"!</i>

00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:13.076
When did they build this stage?

00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:14.536
Tsu?

00:08:14.703 --> 00:08:16.038
Ribbit!

00:08:16.663 --> 00:08:17.539
Ribbit.

00:08:18.207 --> 00:08:20.083
This is like a glorified tight rope.

00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:21.585
She's fast!

00:08:23.378 --> 00:08:24.755
Glitter.

00:08:24.922 --> 00:08:27.466
Here it is!
Here's my chance to show off!

00:08:28.217 --> 00:08:31.637
It's time for my support items
to be in the limelight!

00:08:31.803 --> 00:08:35.224
Look, all you support companies
across the country!

00:08:35.933 --> 00:08:37.433
Wire arrows and…

00:08:37.601 --> 00:08:39.727
hover soles! Glitter!

00:08:39.895 --> 00:08:40.938
You're from the support course?

00:08:41.104 --> 00:08:43.732
What? It's okay to bring in items?

00:08:43.899 --> 00:08:47.611
The hero course undergoes
combat training regularly, right?

00:08:47.778 --> 00:08:49.738
In order to keep things fair,

00:08:49.905 --> 00:08:52.074
we are allow to equip items and costumes,

00:08:52.241 --> 00:08:54.785
as long as we developed them ourselves!

00:08:54.952 --> 00:08:57.246
Or perhaps I should say…

00:08:58.247 --> 00:09:00.374
for those of us in the support course,

00:09:01.583 --> 00:09:03.544
this is the place

00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:07.673
where we can show off our ideas
and skills to companies!

00:09:09.174 --> 00:09:12.970
Come, take a look, all you companies!
Especially the big ones!

00:09:15.013 --> 00:09:18.225
Look at my super cute babies!

00:09:26.984 --> 00:09:27.985
Wow.

00:09:28.151 --> 00:09:29.862
That's so annoying…

00:09:30.028 --> 00:09:31.321
I can't lose!

00:09:31.488 --> 00:09:32.990
That's some misplaced equality!

00:09:34.491 --> 00:09:35.909
Nice…

00:09:38.954 --> 00:09:40.163
<i>A lot of different people</i>

00:09:40.330 --> 00:09:44.501
are working hard
for their chance, huh, Eraser Head?

00:09:44.668 --> 00:09:47.129
What are you idiots stopping for?

00:09:49.715 --> 00:09:52.968
<i>And now, the leader of the pack</i>
<i>is easily getting through first!</i>

00:09:53.677 --> 00:09:56.555
<i>Looks like he's getting fired up.</i>
<i>A slow starter?</i>

00:09:57.306 --> 00:09:59.016
Damn it!

00:10:02.603 --> 00:10:04.563
My older brother
is probably also watching.

00:10:04.730 --> 00:10:07.357
I can't let him see me act uncool!

00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:10.360
<i>That's so uncool!</i>

00:10:10.777 --> 00:10:12.988
That guy in first place is way ahead!

00:10:13.155 --> 00:10:14.615
His Quirk is really strong,

00:10:15.073 --> 00:10:16.909
but his natural athletic ability
and judgment

00:10:17.075 --> 00:10:18.744
are also a cut above everyone else's.

00:10:18.911 --> 00:10:23.665
Of course it is.
That's the Flame Hero, Endeavor's son.

00:10:23.832 --> 00:10:27.586
No wonder! The blood of the guy
second only to All Might, huh?

00:10:27.753 --> 00:10:30.672
There'll be fighting over
who gets him as a sidekick!

00:10:31.590 --> 00:10:35.260
<i>The lead pack is a step ahead, but below</i>
<i>them, everyone's clumped together!</i>

00:10:35.427 --> 00:10:38.138
<i>They haven't announced</i>
<i>how many people will make it through,</i>

00:10:38.305 --> 00:10:40.182
<i>so you can't relax! Push forward!</i>

00:10:41.016 --> 00:10:42.476
Izuku…

00:10:48.190 --> 00:10:50.943
<i>And now, we've quickly</i>
<i>arrived at the final barrier!</i>

00:10:51.109 --> 00:10:52.903
<i>The reality here is…</i>

00:10:53.487 --> 00:10:55.322
<i>that it's a minefield!</i>

00:10:55.489 --> 00:10:58.575
<i>It's set up so that you can tell</i>
<i>where the mines are if you look carefully!</i>

00:10:58.742 --> 00:11:00.827
<i>So you have to exploit your eyes and legs!</i>

00:11:01.453 --> 00:11:05.082
By the way, these landmines are for games,
so they're not that powerful,

00:11:05.624 --> 00:11:09.711
but they're loud and flashy enough
to make you wet your pants!

00:11:09.878 --> 00:11:11.213
That depends on the person.

00:11:11.713 --> 00:11:13.924
<i>First place is already there?</i>

00:11:14.550 --> 00:11:16.593
<i>Faster!</i>

00:11:20.305 --> 00:11:23.976
<i>I see. This is an obstacle that puts</i>
<i>those in the lead at a disadvantage.</i>

00:11:24.142 --> 00:11:25.811
<i>Trying to make it entertaining, huh?</i>

00:11:30.148 --> 00:11:31.817
This doesn't affect me!

00:11:33.986 --> 00:11:38.198
Bastard, don't declare
war to the wrong person!

00:11:39.616 --> 00:11:41.785
<i>And now,</i>
<i>we've got someone new in the lead!</i>

00:11:41.952 --> 00:11:46.039
<i>Rejoice, mass media! It's the kind</i>
<i>of development you guys love!</i>

00:11:48.417 --> 00:11:49.793
<i>Hey, hey, hey,</i>

00:11:49.960 --> 00:11:52.171
<i>the rest of the pack is</i>
<i>also speeding up!</i>

00:11:52.337 --> 00:11:53.422
<i>However!</i>

00:11:53.589 --> 00:11:56.508
<i>Even as they push and pull at each other,</i>
<i>can the two at the top remain in the lead?</i>

00:12:07.019 --> 00:12:08.562
It's far…

00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:13.609
But there's still stuff I have to do!

00:12:22.284 --> 00:12:25.204
I'm gonna borrow your idea, Kacchan!

00:12:32.377 --> 00:12:34.421
<i>There's a huge explosion at the back!</i>

00:12:34.922 --> 00:12:36.840
<i>What's with that force?</i>

00:12:43.597 --> 00:12:44.556
What?

00:12:44.723 --> 00:12:47.142
<i>Was it an accident,</i>
<i>or did he do it on purpose?</i>

00:12:47.309 --> 00:12:52.397
<i>Class A's Midoriya is in</i>
<i>hot pursuit with that blast!</i>

00:12:56.777 --> 00:12:58.779
<i>Landmines used for games…</i>

00:12:58.946 --> 00:13:01.448
<i>The type with fuses that</i>
<i>go off if you step on them.</i>

00:13:01.615 --> 00:13:03.659
<i>They're not that powerful,</i>

00:13:03.825 --> 00:13:06.203
<i>but if I lose my balance</i>
<i>and set off a bunch of them,</i>

00:13:06.370 --> 00:13:07.996
<i>I'll lose a lot of time.</i>

00:13:08.455 --> 00:13:10.374
<i>If I take injuries</i>
<i>and stamina into account,</i>

00:13:10.541 --> 00:13:13.168
<i>it'd be better to slow down</i>
<i>and avoid them.</i>

00:13:13.961 --> 00:13:16.505
<i>The jumpers can't jump carelessly either,</i>

00:13:16.672 --> 00:13:19.716
<i>and the further ahead you are,</i>
<i>the more landmines you'll have to avoid.</i>

00:13:20.175 --> 00:13:22.761
<i>They probably can't go</i>
<i>very fast with all the obstacles.</i>

00:13:23.554 --> 00:13:24.680
<i>Look carefully!</i>

00:13:24.847 --> 00:13:26.932
<i>The places where those in front avoided…</i>

00:13:27.599 --> 00:13:30.561
<i>Everyone was the most careful</i>
<i>around the entrance.</i>

00:13:30.727 --> 00:13:32.396
<i>There are a lot of landmines left.</i>

00:13:32.563 --> 00:13:33.564
<i>It'll be fine.</i>

00:13:33.730 --> 00:13:35.357
-What's Midoriya doing?
-<i>Don't be impatient here!</i>

00:13:35.524 --> 00:13:37.401
<i>In the lead are Bakugo and Todoroki!</i>

00:13:37.568 --> 00:13:40.237
<i>They'll get through the last barrier soon!</i>

00:13:40.404 --> 00:13:41.280
All right.

00:13:44.408 --> 00:13:45.993
I'm gonna borrow your idea, Kacchan!

00:13:46.159 --> 00:13:48.662
<i>Super explosive speed turbo!</i>

00:13:55.377 --> 00:13:56.461
That's…

00:13:57.171 --> 00:14:01.258
<i>Class A's Midoriya is in hot pursuit</i>
<i>with that blast!</i>

00:14:03.468 --> 00:14:05.804
<i>Actually, he's taken the lead!</i>

00:14:05.971 --> 00:14:08.056
LET'S FIGHT FOR VICTORY!!

00:14:08.223 --> 00:14:10.434
<i>I flew just like I'd planned,</i>

00:14:10.601 --> 00:14:12.269
<i>but there's so much force!</i>

00:14:12.436 --> 00:14:13.437
<i>And…</i>

00:14:13.979 --> 00:14:16.231
<i>I didn't think about landing!</i>

00:14:18.025 --> 00:14:19.067
Deku!

00:14:19.234 --> 00:14:21.778
Don't go ahead of me!

00:14:23.614 --> 00:14:25.741
<i>This'll give those in the back a path…</i>

00:14:26.491 --> 00:14:28.535
<i>but I don't have time</i>
<i>to worry about what's behind me!</i>

00:14:28.869 --> 00:14:31.872
The two <i>formerly</i> in the lead have
stopped trying to slow each other down

00:14:32.039 --> 00:14:33.790
<i>and are chasing Midoriya!</i>

00:14:33.957 --> 00:14:36.752
<i>Now that they have a common enemy,</i>
<i>they've stopped fighting!</i>

00:14:36.919 --> 00:14:39.338
<i>The fight's not over yet, though!</i>

00:14:39.505 --> 00:14:41.256
<i>What are you saying?</i>

00:14:42.508 --> 00:14:43.425
<i>Oh no…</i>

00:14:43.592 --> 00:14:44.676
<i>I'm losing speed!</i>

00:14:44.843 --> 00:14:45.928
<i>That's not surprising.</i>

00:14:46.094 --> 00:14:47.471
<i>They'll overtake me in an instant!</i>

00:14:48.055 --> 00:14:49.723
<i>Thinking about the time I'd lose landing,</i>

00:14:49.890 --> 00:14:51.934
<i>there's no way I'd be able</i>
<i>to take back the lead.</i>

00:14:52.351 --> 00:14:55.062
<i>Damn it! No! Don't let go!</i>

00:14:55.521 --> 00:14:58.899
<i>Grab hold of that chance you got to get</i>
<i>in front of these two,</i>

00:14:59.066 --> 00:15:01.401
<i>and don't let go!</i>

00:15:02.861 --> 00:15:03.987
<i>If I can't take back the lead,</i>

00:15:04.947 --> 00:15:07.741
<i>then I can't let them get ahead of me!</i>

00:15:15.457 --> 00:15:18.794
<i>Midoriya swiftly blocks those behind him!</i>

00:15:19.127 --> 00:15:21.797
<i>Would you believe it?</i>
<i>He cleared the minefield in an instant!</i>

00:15:24.716 --> 00:15:27.177
<i>Eraser Head, your class is amazing!</i>

00:15:27.344 --> 00:15:29.304
What're you teaching them?

00:15:29.471 --> 00:15:31.431
I didn't do anything.

00:15:32.724 --> 00:15:35.936
<i>They got each other fired up on their own.</i>

00:15:37.020 --> 00:15:40.190
<i>-U.A. sports festival, first-year stage!</i>
<i>-Not listening!</i>

00:15:40.357 --> 00:15:45.821
<i>Who could've predicted the developments</i>
<i>at the beginning or this conclusion?</i>

00:15:46.989 --> 00:15:50.701
<i>Right now, the first person back</i>
<i>in the stadium is that man…</i>

00:15:52.369 --> 00:15:55.664
<i>Izuku Midoriya's made a huge splash!</i>

00:16:01.378 --> 00:16:03.338
Izu…

00:16:05.924 --> 00:16:07.968
Hey, that kid's…

00:16:09.011 --> 00:16:11.972
Oh yeah. If I remember correctly,
he's from last year…

00:16:12.139 --> 00:16:13.182
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

00:16:15.976 --> 00:16:17.978
This brat is…

00:16:49.092 --> 00:16:53.305
<i>This sports festival is a competition</i>
<i>where they have to aim for the top,</i>

00:16:53.472 --> 00:16:55.474
<i>even if it means defeating</i>
<i>their friends and classmates.</i>

00:16:56.892 --> 00:16:59.895
<i>Modern heroes depend a lot</i>
<i>on their popularity,</i>

00:17:00.062 --> 00:17:04.358
<i>so they need to have that desire</i>
<i>to be above all the others.</i>

00:17:05.776 --> 00:17:08.569
<i>At your core, you are a hero</i>
<i>who wants to help others.</i>

00:17:09.445 --> 00:17:11.823
<i>That is why I chose you,</i>

00:17:13.116 --> 00:17:17.538
<i>but I thought that was also your weakness.</i>

00:17:20.958 --> 00:17:22.792
<i>I was worrying over absolutely nothing!</i>

00:17:22.960 --> 00:17:23.961
<i>Sorry!</i>

00:17:24.127 --> 00:17:26.797
<i>You should still try to stop</i>
<i>being such a crybaby, though.</i>

00:17:27.881 --> 00:17:28.924
What do you think?

00:17:29.383 --> 00:17:32.094
First of all, Midoriya's stock
will climb fast.

00:17:32.553 --> 00:17:35.013
However,
he still has not shown his Quirk yet,

00:17:35.180 --> 00:17:36.515
so it's hard to predict what will happen.

00:17:37.099 --> 00:17:42.145
If you took on management of an agency,
how would you market him? Opinions?

00:17:42.312 --> 00:17:43.272
What do you think?

00:17:43.438 --> 00:17:45.023
His appearance is out.

00:17:45.399 --> 00:17:47.359
If he were particular
about his abilities or aesthetics,

00:17:47.526 --> 00:17:49.486
we could highlight those parts,

00:17:49.653 --> 00:17:52.531
but without the raw material to work with…

00:17:52.698 --> 00:17:53.740
<i>That business course!</i>

00:17:53.907 --> 00:17:55.617
<i>They never change, huh?</i>

00:17:56.618 --> 00:17:57.619
<i>The business course!</i>

00:17:57.786 --> 00:18:00.664
<i>There is not really any benefit to them</i>
<i>participating in the sports festival!</i>

00:18:01.123 --> 00:18:01.999
<i>Therefore,</i>

00:18:02.165 --> 00:18:06.712
<i>they cultivate their instincts by selling</i>
<i>things or doing marketing simulations!</i>

00:18:06.879 --> 00:18:08.172
<i>They've got a lot of free time!</i>

00:18:13.677 --> 00:18:14.636
Again…

00:18:14.928 --> 00:18:16.054
Damn!

00:18:16.638 --> 00:18:18.098
Damn it!

00:18:19.349 --> 00:18:22.311
<i>And now,</i>
<i>they're finishing one after another!</i>

00:18:22.477 --> 00:18:26.648
<i>We'll make a list of the results later,</i>
<i>but for now, good work!</i>

00:18:31.320 --> 00:18:33.530
Deku! You were amazing!

00:18:33.989 --> 00:18:35.157
Uraraka?

00:18:35.324 --> 00:18:36.700
First place is amazing!

00:18:36.867 --> 00:18:38.577
That's so frustrating, dang it!

00:18:38.744 --> 00:18:40.537
It was just…

00:18:42.831 --> 00:18:44.625
<i>I was just lucky!</i>

00:18:44.958 --> 00:18:48.003
<i>I just happened to be able to use</i>
<i>something I thought I could use.</i>

00:18:48.587 --> 00:18:50.714
<i>What's amazing was my luck.</i>

00:18:51.840 --> 00:18:53.425
<i>It was a lucky punch.</i>

00:18:56.386 --> 00:19:00.641
<i>My real ability will be tested after this.</i>

00:19:05.521 --> 00:19:06.939
This isn't how it was supposed to…

00:19:08.315 --> 00:19:09.733
I killed two birds with one stone!

00:19:09.900 --> 00:19:11.235
I'm a genius!

00:19:11.818 --> 00:19:13.737
You're the worst!

