00:20:07.916 --> 00:20:10.460
<i>The press cavalry will be all over it!</i>

00:20:10.627 --> 00:20:12.212
<i>Give it your all!</i>

00:20:15.007 --> 00:20:18.802
<i>Now then, here is the second game.</i>
<i>I already know what it is,</i>

00:20:19.219 --> 00:20:22.055
<i>but what could it be?</i>

00:20:22.431 --> 00:20:25.767
<i>I just said it, and now here it is…</i>

00:20:26.768 --> 00:20:28.103
A cavalry battle?

00:20:28.270 --> 00:20:29.605
I'm bad at those…

00:20:29.771 --> 00:20:32.774
It's not an individual event,
so I wonder how it'll work…

00:20:33.108 --> 00:20:34.443
<i>Let me explain.</i>

00:20:35.110 --> 00:20:39.865
<i>The participants can form teams</i>
<i>of two to four people as they wish.</i>

00:20:40.324 --> 00:20:43.493
<i>It's basically the same</i>
<i>as a regular cavalry battle,</i>

00:20:44.036 --> 00:20:45.746
<i>but the one thing that's different is…</i>

00:20:46.205 --> 00:20:47.623
<i>based on the results of the last game,</i>

00:20:47.789 --> 00:20:50.417
<i>each person</i>
<i>has been assigned a point value.</i>

00:20:50.751 --> 00:20:53.462
A point-based system
like the entrance exam, huh?

00:20:53.629 --> 00:20:54.963
That's easy to understand.

00:20:55.380 --> 00:20:56.256
In other words,

00:20:56.423 --> 00:20:59.218
each team is worth different points
depending on who's on the team!

00:20:59.384 --> 00:21:00.719
I see!

00:21:01.428 --> 00:21:04.223
<i>You guys don't hold back</i>
<i>even though I'm talking, huh?</i>

00:21:05.098 --> 00:21:09.436
<i>Yes, that's right! And the points assigned</i>
<i>go up by five starting from the bottom.</i>

00:21:09.603 --> 00:21:14.149
<i>So 42nd place gets five points,</i>
<i>and 41st gets ten points!</i>

00:21:15.025 --> 00:21:18.153
<i>And the point value</i>
<i>assigned to first place is…</i>

00:21:18.487 --> 00:21:19.655
<i>ten million!</i>

00:21:21.323 --> 00:21:23.742
Ten million?

00:21:24.243 --> 00:21:25.994
<i>Ten million, huh?</i>

00:21:26.620 --> 00:21:29.581
<i>In other words, if you take down</i>
<i>the first place player's team…</i>

00:21:29.748 --> 00:21:33.043
<i>…you can stand at the top</i>
<i>no matter what place you're in!</i>

00:21:34.878 --> 00:21:35.879
<i>That's right.</i>

00:21:37.005 --> 00:21:38.674
<i>It's survival of the fittest,</i>

00:21:38.841 --> 00:21:41.593
<i>with a chance for those</i>
<i>at the bottom to overthrow the top!</i>

